The paper discusses the use of transfer learning with deep neural networks for computer vision systems, which is a common topic in the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the effectiveness of convolutional feature extraction and fine-tuning of overparameterized models, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses generalization performance on out-of-distribution data, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
